asis of this book. Libraries, for example, are in partnership with Google to better organize and retrieve digital information. New tools in the area of social networking are being applied daily in libraries as research librarians reach out to their users and meet them in their spaces, thus integrating themselves into the campus fabric. This book provides an excellent historical overview of the issues and concerns of research librarians around digital information and knowledge management. After reading it, those wishing to learn about current applications and challenges should consult the journal literature.
